Patch to apply to decoders/aac/tns.c (the symlinked libhelix-aac source):

- Keep AMIGA_AAC_DISABLE_TNS_TEST as an early return fallback in TNSFilter.
- Replace the U64 hi32/lo32 accumulator usage in FilterRegion with signed
  long long scalar Q20 arithmetic. The Arduino libhelix assembly.h declares
  U64 with little-endian lo32/hi32 field order, so tns.c corrupts sum64 on
  big-endian m68k when it writes sum64.r.hi32 and sum64.r.lo32 directly.
- Replace DecodeLPCCoefs' MULSHIFT32 use with an explicit signed 64-bit
  high-word multiply helper for m68k fixed-point parity.
- Avoid left-shifting negative 32-bit ints in the Q20 accumulator path; convert
  the signed 64-bit accumulator back to int by selecting bits [51:20] via an
  unsigned right shift, then perform the original high-word saturation test.

Suggested code substitutions:

static int TNSMulShift32(int x, int y)
{
    return (int)(((long long)x * (long long)y) >> 32);
}

static int TNSQ20ToInt(long long v)
{
    unsigned long long u = (unsigned long long)v;
    return (int)(u >> FBITS_LPC_COEFS);
}

static int TNSClipQ20ToInt(long long v)
{
    long long hi = v >> 32;
    int y = TNSQ20ToInt(v);

    if ((hi >> 31) != (hi >> (FBITS_LPC_COEFS - 1)))
        y = (int)((hi >> 31) ^ 0x7fffffff);
    return y;
}

In DecodeLPCCoefs(), change:
    b[i] = a[i] - (MULSHIFT32(t, a[m - i - 1]) << 1);
to:
    b[i] = a[i] - (TNSMulShift32(t, a[m - i - 1]) << 1);

In FilterRegion(), replace the U64 sum64/hi32/lo32 path with:
    long long sum64;
    ...
    y = *audioCoef;
    sum64 = ((long long)y) << FBITS_LPC_COEFS;
    for (j = order - 1; j > 0; j--) {
        sum64 += (long long)hist[j] * (long long)a[j];
        hist[j] = hist[j - 1];
    }
    sum64 += (long long)hist[0] * (long long)a[0];
    y = TNSClipQ20ToInt(sum64);

At the top of TNSFilter(), keep the fallback:
#ifdef AMIGA_AAC_DISABLE_TNS_TEST
    (void)aacDecInfo;
    (void)ch;
    return 0;
#endif
